---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Black hole mass";
import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Black hole mass</h1>

    <p>
      Black hole mass (M_BH) is a fundamental parameter describing the central supermassive black hole in galaxies. It is measured via reverberation mapping, single-epoch virial estimators for broad-line AGN, stellar or gas dynamics in nearby galaxies, and scaling relations with host properties.
    </p>

    <h2>In the context of AGN environment studies</h2>
    <p>
      Studies test whether M_BH correlates with large-scale environment (halo mass) beyond what is expected from host-galaxy scaling relations. Mountrichas et al. (2026) report no significant variation of halo mass with M_BH for their X-ray BLAGN sample once host-galaxy properties are controlled for<sup><a href="/pages/mountrichas_2026_agn_environments">1</a></sup>.
    </p>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Mountrichas G., Carrera F. J., Shankar F., Georgakakis A. (2026). arXiv:2603.11169.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
